## ğŸ¯ A SMART Business Goal:

Executives at Jimmyâ€™s Auto LLC. Have proposed these goals while implementing a customer service chatbot: 

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  27% elimination of customer service roles, achieving employee salary savings of $565,000 within the first 6 months. 
Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  $20,000 / yr. reduction in office space costs. 
Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  40% reduction in customer service employee training costs by implementing online resources, including virtual demos and AI-generated documentation. 
Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Following latest market studies â€“ transition 35% of customers to the chatbot for basic customer support and sales inquiries withing the first 6 months.

**âœ… Use Case 90-Day Outcomes:**

Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  The LLC decided on a more conservative approach to reducing customer service staff to only 7% per 30 days for a total of 21% rather than 27% at 90 days. 
Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  This allowed for a safer transition and kept key employees incase the chatbot deployment did not go as expected. 
Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Letting some employees work remotely allowed for the reduction in office space to go on as planned. 
Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  The reduction in customer service employee training happened as planned, though outcomes on how well employees were trained still need to be evaluated. 
Â·Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Full 6 month analysis not complete, but customer adoption has been steady, with long-time customers still more likely to opt to speak to a human customer services resource.

**ğŸ” Why It Was Well-Constructed:**

The executive team made SMART goals that were timebound with specific quantifiable goals tied to these timelines. 

The use case was specific, and therefore, before engaging with internal stakeholders, in-depth research could be done on how other companies had successfully implemented AI chatbots for similar use cases, as well as what the results were. This helped to guide expectations in a realistic way.


